title: ursa_minor_(constellation)
body:
Ursa Minor (the Lesser [[Bear]], also known as the [i]Little Dipper[/i]) is a [[constellation]] located in the Northern celestial hemisphere. It is best known for its brightest star [[Polaris (star)|]], the Pole Star, located at the end of the bear's "tail" or the dipper's "handle". Its name, the [i]Lesser Bear[/i], refers to and contrasts it with nearby [[Ursa Major (constellation)|]], the [i]Greater Bear[/i].

Like the [[Big Dipper]], Ursa Minor consists of seven stars and can be distinguished by its "handle": the former is bent downward, while the latter is bent upward.

h5. Examples
* !asset #21150854: Shape
* !post #2724830

h5. Neighboring constellations
* [[Camelopardalis (constellation)|]]
* [[Cepheus (constellation)|]]
* [[Draco (constellation)|]]

title: red_ribbon_army
body:
The [b]Red Ribbon Army[/b] are a semi-reoccuring antagonist faction in [[Dragon Ball]].

Originally debuting in the eponymous arc of [[Dragon Ball (classic)|the original]], they were a huge private army led by [[Red (dragon ball)|General Red]] who searched for the [[Dragon Ball (object)|]]s to achieve world domination. After their destruction at the hand of [[Son Goku]], [[Dr. Gero (dragon ball)|]], head scientist of the Red Ribbon Army, returned in the Android Arc of [[Dragon Ball Z]], aiming to rebuild the Red Ribbon Army to exact revenge on the Z Fighters. They would later return in [[Dragon Ball Super]] [[Dragon Ball Super Super Hero|Super Hero]], disguised as Red Pharmaceuticals, under the command of Red's son [[Magenta (dragon ball)|]], recruiting Gero's grandson [[Dr. Hedo]] to create them a new set of androids and once more achieve world domination.

Their logo is a red ribbon with an "R" on both ends.

title: golden_boy
body:
[i][b]GOLDEN BOY[/b][/i] (stylized in all caps) is a Japanese sex comedy manga series written and illustrated by [[Egawa Tatsuya]]. 

It was serialized in Shueisha's seinen manga magazine Super Jump from 1992 to 1997, with its chapters collected in ten tankōbon volumes. It tells the story of [[Ooe Kintarou]], a 25-year-old freeter "travelling student", who despite having met the requirements for a law degree, left [[tokyo_(city)|Tokyo]] University without graduating. 

Kintaro is living freely, roaming Japan from town to town, job to job. During his travels, Kintaro meets several women whose lives he dramatically changes, despite poor first impressions. He constantly observes and studies the people and events around him, recording his findings in a notebook he carries on his belt.

Parts of the manga were adapted into a six-episode original video animation (OVA) series produced by Shueisha and KSS in 1995. In North America, it was first licensed by ADV Films in 1996. ADV's license to the series expired in 2007 and was later acquired by Media Blasters. Media Blasters lost the license in 2012 and it was later acquired by Discotek Media. A sequel to the manga, [[Golden Boy II]], was serialized in Business Jump from September 2010 to May 2011.

title: bamboo_curtain
body:
Bamboo curtains, especially those hanging at the door or window, are a type of bamboo weaving craft.

During the Tang Dynasty in China, the production of bamboo curtains was introduced to Korea and Japan. In the Edo period, Tokyo bamboo curtains became famous due to the ukiyo-e prints by Kitagawa Utamaro. In 1983, Japanese Edo curtains were designated as a traditional craft of Tokyo. 

In 2013, Korea's bamboo curtain craftsmanship - known as "najeongsa" - was designated as Important Intangible Cultural Heritage No.114 by the Cultural Heritage Administration of Korea.

title: qian_li_jiangshan_tu_(wuhua_mixin)
body:
Qian li Jiangshan tu is a character in [[Wuhua Mixin]], personifying the painting created by the Chinese Northern Song dynasty painter Wang Ximeng which is now housed in the Palace Museum in Beijing.

Qian li Jiangshan tu is depicted as a gentle young man in appearance. His demeanor is as gentle as jade, and his approach to life is meticulous and methodical, much like the precise brushwork in the painting.

title: saraswati_veena
body: Saraswati veena is a type of ancient Indian string [[instrument]] (which are called veena). It also belongs to the [[lute_(instrument)|lute]] family. It's named after the [[hindu mythology|Hindu goddess]] [[Saraswati]], who is usually depicted holding or playing the instrument.

title: geomungo
body: Geomungo is a traditional Korean plucked long [[zither]] [[instrument]], usually played while seated on the floor with a pencil-size bamboo stick plectrum. It's similar to Korean [[gayageum]], Chinese [[guzheng]] and Japanese [[koto_(instrument)|koto]]. The main visual difference is that it has 16 convex rectangular frets and 6 strings (modern versions may have more), 3 of which are over frets. Strings are attached to the body by long cords that are arranged in an ornamental manner.

title: say_the_line_bart_(meme)
body:
References to a scene in [[The Simpsons]] Season 5 Episode 12 "Bart Gets Famous". In the episode, [[Bart Simpson]] becomes famous for quipping the one-liner "I didn't do it" after causing a catastrophic stage accident while on live broadcast.

The scene for this meme is when Bart is in class and all his classmates (and teacher) look at him excitedly, wanting him to repeat his famous line. His friend [[Milhouse Van Houten]] nudges him: "[b]Say the line, Bart[/b]". He does so begrudgingly, weary of repeating the same line over and over again. The entire classroom cheers.

h4. External link

* "The scene in Frinkiac":[https://frinkiac.com/caption/S05E12/1020952]

title: gena_the_crocodile_and_his_friends
body:
1966 soviet novel by Eduard Uspensky, later adapted into a series of animated stop-motion films by Soyuzmultfilm.
The series follows Gena the Crocodile, who originally works as a zoo animal, in his various encounters with the citizens of Moscow and Cheburashka.


Its most well known character is [[Cheburashka]], who became a massive cultural icon in Soviet Russia and the countries following its dissolution.
He's also garnered popularity in Japan due to an animated film series broadcasted in its theaters from the summer of 2001 to the spring of 2002.
Cheburashka and Gena have since appeared in postage stamps, coins and as the mascots of Russia in Olympic events, as well as in tons of merchandise and a few remakes.

h5. Main characters

* [[Gena the Crocodile]]

title: phoenix_tree
body:
The Phoenix tree, also known as "Phoenix tree," is a deciduous tall tree that can grow up to 15 meters high. It has a straight trunk with smooth green bark. Originally from China, it is cultivated in various provinces throughout the country for landscaping and ornamental purposes.

Chinese people have long regarded the Phoenix tree as a symbol of auspiciousness. It is believed that the phoenix enjoys perching on the Phoenix tree, so in ancient times, both imperial palaces and private residences liked to plant these trees in the hope of attracting the phoenix.

The lush green leaves of the Phoenix tree have strong resistance to sulfur dioxide and hydrogen fluoride, making it a good tree species for landscaping gardens and industrial greening, and it can also be planted as roadside trees.

body:
The logo of the [[Patreon]] platform.

This is typically used as a watermark and placed next to an artist's name or Patreon page, although it can also be used in clever ways such as to censor a character or be incorporated in an image some other way.

Use this tag instead of the [[Patreon]] tag for instances of the Patreon logo.

h4. Present and past logos

body:
[i][b]Pecteilis radiata[/b][/i] (commonly known as fringed orchid or white egret flower) is a species of [[orchid]] with characteristic flowers that resemble a bird, namely the [[egret (animal)|]], with its wings spread.

body:
Japan-based indie band.

title: makarov_(pumpkin_mishka)_(girls'_frontline)
body:
[[Makarov (girls' frontline)|]]'s first skin from [[Girls' Frontline]], as part of the 'Halloween Carnival' skin collection in 2016 through shop purchase.

It's a [[Jack-O'-Lantern]]-themed [[Halloween costume]], with a [[pumpkin hat]] with an [[axe]] and [[sword]] embedded, [[bandage over one eye|bandages over her right eye]], and her hair in [[long hair|long]] [[low twintails]]. Her attire consists simply of a [[white]] [[collared shirt]] with a [[bolt (hardware)|]] in her right arm, a [[red ascot]], [[suspenders]] with her [[multicolored skirt|multicolored]] [[black skirt|black]], [[orange skirt|orange]] and [[blue skirt|blue]] [[layered skirt]], and [[bandaged leg]]s acting as her footwear. She has a [[ball and chain restraint]] on both legs, and a [[stuffed animal]] she is pointing her gun at.

body:
パフュームグラブ

A pair of gauntlet-like compact gears made and used by [[Isis Egret|Isis Egret]]. An AI system is installed to it, and like Steed, it speaks Japanese, too.

Perfume Grab is actually a spelling mistake of Perfume Glove.

title: glumi_(iron_saga)
body:
[[Iron Saga]] character. The former prince of the Grand Duchy. Why he left his homeland is a mystery. He met the Desert Bandit's leader Katarina and became her fellow chief mate. Although he is always callous and sharp-tongued, he is surprisingly a gentle person.

h4. External links

* "Iron Saga Wiki: Gurumi":https://ironsaga.fandom.com/wiki/Gurumi

title: wynonna_(iron_saga)
body:
[[Iron Saga]] character. One of the Curia Machinery's templar knights. A mischievous denpa girl who wields the ability to manipulate "machine spirits" and has a bad habit of grumbling. During the Purification War, she defeated Tüzel by herself.

h4. External links

* "Iron Saga Wiki: Vinora":https://ironsaga.fandom.com/wiki/Vinora Deleted
* "Iron Saga Wiki: Winona":https://ironsaga.fandom.com/wiki/Winona

title: arseille_(iron_saga)
body:
[[Iron Saga]] character. The princess of the Gungnir Duchy. A straightforward and brave person who hates beating around the bush. She always fights her enemies fair and square.

h4. External links

* "Iron Saga Wiki: Arselle":https://ironsaga.fandom.com/wiki/Arselle

title: vivian_kirastar_(iron_saga)
body:
[[Iron Saga]] character. While Kira Star may seem like a young girl, she is actually a resourceful bounty hunter travelling around the world. She is very expressive on what she wants and is always the noisiest of the bunch. She is always filled with energy and others find it difficult to dislike her. A reliable person except when push comes to shove.

h4. External links

* "Iron Saga Wiki: Kira Star":https://ironsaga.fandom.com/wiki/Kira_Star

title: becas_shannam_(iron_saga)
body:
Protagonist of [[Iron Saga]]. A C-Class Mercenary with with money problems. Has a misterious past. He works for a shady scientist lady.

He meets and befriends [[Slokai (iron saga)|]] during the story.

His mechas are [[Vassago (iron saga)|]], [[Vergil (iron saga)|]], and [[Infinity (iron saga)|]].

title: nodowa_(gorget)
body:
[i]Nodowa[/i] (喉輪, lit. throat ring) is a crescent-shaped [[Japanese armor|Japanese]] analog of a [[gorget]]. It is worn like a bib, tied around the neck to protect the wearer's throat and upper chest. 

When the throat guard is attached to the [[menpoo|menpo]], it is called a [i]sage[/i] (下げ) or [i]tare[/i] (垂).

title: candlestand
body:
A device that holds one or more [[candle]]s in place, also known as a [b]candlestick[/b] or [b]candleholder[/b]. A candlestand for several candles is called a [b][[candelabra]][/b]. They can be simple or highly ornate, and they can be made of various materials, from wood to brass to silver.  A subtype of candlestick is [b]chamberstick[/b], a short candlestick with a large pan to catch wax and handle, that is used in carrying a candle to the bedroom.

The [[chandelier]] originated as a large candlestand designed to be suspended from a ceiling.

The [[menorah]] is a candelabra with particular religious significance.

h4. See also
* [[candlelight]]

title: hisui_(cookie)
body:
* !asset #21018560
* !asset #21018561

Voice of [[Reisen Udongein Inaba]] in [[cookie_(touhou)|Cookie☆☆ S3]] and [[Kaenbyou Rin]] in Nabe☆. As Reisen, she has [[swept bangs]] and a single bent ear, often [[breathing fire]] from a random one-shot joke in 2015. She is still active as a [[virtual youtuber]].

She was initially the least popular character of Cookie☆☆ S3, with almost no fan art or MADs. However in 2016, a single user by the name of [[Ants (cookie)|]] began posting MAD ranking videos as if she was a popular character like [[Majime-kun]]. Other users began ironically making MADs starring Hisui, which would then get added into Ants's rankings, which would then cause more people to watch them. This began the "Unprecedented HSI姉貴 Boom" where derivative characters with almost no connection to anything Hisui herself ever did were made. 

This rapid escalation also caused a number of running jokes. One that carried over from Reisen is fake or detachable ears, except that Hisui's aren't and ends with her comedically spewing blood everywhere. Another is Reisen's affinity for guns, except Hisui prefers shotguns alongside [[Rurima (cookie)|]]. Her voice remixes include [[chirumiru]] and [[shin takarajima (song)|]].

Parody derivative characters include:
* [[fake hisui (cookie)|Although-she-is-a-fake-but-she-looks-like-a-nice-person Hisui-san]]: an intentionally poorly drawn version that is animated extremely well as a joke
* [[Metal Hisui (cookie)|]]: a robot version that can shoot lasers that turn anything to metal and fly. Created by a relatively unknown (at the time) MAD maker named [[Jiko Mujun]].
* [[Dragon Hisui (cookie)|]]: Hisui's fire breathing joke taken to the extreme
* [[Black Hisui (cookie)|]]: A [[dark-skinned female|dark-skinned]] and lewder version. 
* [[Meat Hisui (cookie)|]]: created by a MAD maker known by Ishikei, she is now completely meat. 
* Child / baby Hisui: an [[aged down]] version. Often NSFL. 

h4. External Links
* Youtube channel: https://www.youtube.com/@t_hisui

title: shiriri_(cookie)
body:
* !asset #21118258

[[Niconico]] based [[Cookie (touhou)|]]☆ content creator. Started out as a MAD maker in 2016 before moving into directing in 2018, making SpeCa☆ and Gorgonzola☆. Was first targeted during the Cookie Freezing Festival of 2018 but survived. He is male, but his avatar is [[androgynous]].

One of the most important content creators on the site during the later part of the Cookie fandom. His MADs were all extremely high quality no matter the subject, mixing Cookie with everything from Jojo to Undertale. Created CTV, later handing it off to [[AaliyahRaylenard]]. He attracted a huge amount of fans and haters, as others were jealous of his rapid rise. This was compounded when he became a director of Cookie's most shitposty voice dramas, and people began accusing him of making his own MAD material. A rumor that he was a wanted [[karasawa_takahiro|HaseKara]] member began to spread, and on December 5th 2018 he was completely doxxed not by Cookie fans but by the HaseKara community. His name, age, photo, home address, university, and arrest for producing [[LSD]], and he changed his account names to "Cemetery" and disappeared. His doxxing left an extremely bad feeling in the Cookie community, later inspiring [[Jiko Mujun]] to incorporate it in Self Contradiction☆.

Nicovideo: https://www.nicovideo.jp/user/57421227
Twitter: https://twitter.com/RebelliousRIM
Cookie Wiki Article: https://w.atwiki.jp/cookie_kaisetu/pages/1186.html

Large oceanic species of [[fish]] from the tribe [b]Thunnini[/b] used as [[food]] and for recreational [[fishing]]. title: crisis_moon_compact
body:
The [[heart brooch]] that [[Super Sailor Moon]] uses to transform in all iterations of the fourth season of [[Bishoujo Senshi Sailor Moon]]. [[tsukino usagi|Usagi]] and [[Chibi Usa]] (with her Chibi Moon Compact) both shout "Moon Crisis, Make Up" to morph into their Sailor Senshi identities. This is the only transformation sequence in the series that involves two characters simultaneously.

You want to be able to see the brooch's details up close to make sure it's not a different type of compact that Sailor Moon uses. If you cannot see what it is, or it's drawn so far away that it's rendered as a generic brooch, don't use this tag. It is especially difficult to tell this and her [[Cosmic Heart Compact]] apart from far away, but the easiest difference is that this has gold wings on the heart's sides whereas the other doesn't.

The compact "looks like this":https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/sailormoon/images/2/24/A-crisis-moon-compact.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120322220828 when up close.

body:

There are actually two distinct designs for this brooch; "one":https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/sailormoon/images/e/ea/Tumblr_nyho9o9tnC1qjkedbo5_1280.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20160927125923 from the manga and [[bishoujo senshi sailor moon crystal|Crystal]], and the "other":https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/sailormoon/images/3/3f/48.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20200601141704 from the 90s anime. You want to be able to see the brooch's details up close to make sure it's not a different type of compact that Sailor Moon uses. If you cannot see what it is, or it's drawn so far away that it's rendered as a generic brooch, don't use this tag.

Not to be confused with the [[Transformation Pen]]s that the [[Inner Senshi]] use to transform into their Sailor identities.

body:

She is a serious and diligent editor and a low-level troubadour working for the publishing company "[i]Sword&Friend Company's second editorial department[/i]", tasked with the job of revising their masterpiece "The Dragon Book". title: candy_candy_(series)

title: jiko_mujun
body:
* !asset #21106115
* !asset #21106111
* !asset #21106113

Director, animator, editor, and voice of [[Usami Renko]] of his self-titled [[cookie (touhou)|Marisa and Alice's Self Contradiction☆]]. Previously a well-respected MAD maker best known for creating [[Metal Hisui (cookie)|]], he was later leaked to be [[xxx_(nicoseiga530226)|]]. Arguably the most controversial director since [[Hazuna Rio]], as Self Contradiction☆ created a massive upheaval in the Cookie community with crossing accusations of fame, purpose, and what was even the point of Cookie anymore. 

After abandoning his old art account in 2014, he began slowly making MADs in 2015. He liked [[Asatsuki (cookie)|]] and was uniquely good at animation for a MAD maker, but contemporaries noticed that he was hard to contact as he almost never checked DMs. Self Contradiction☆ is a partly autobiographical work of both his and [[Fumei (cookie)|]]'s experiences in the Cookie community that he started writing in 2018. When it was released in 2020 it instantly became the most controversial voice drama since the original, as it was an extremely harsh critique of every aspect of the community. Both antis and supporters of the drama began attacking each other and him, and he ended up being accused of chasing fame himself and got doxxed at his appearance at a small art festival in Lisbon, Portugal.

title: mishou_kazuya_(cookie)
body:
* !asset #21105952

Director of [[cookie (touhou)|Kasu☆]] and semi-professional musician. Originally wanted to do BGM for [[Taisa (cookie)|]] if she made another voice drama, but became a director after Taisa confirmed her retirement. His arrogance before and after his voice drama was released led to a lot of negative impressions of him, and people accused him of just chasing the fame of Cookie☆. Even though he had said he was retiring from Cookie☆  afterwards, he did one more livestream with [[Eska (cookie)|]], so her fans got mad and insulted him again.

To this day he is mostly considered to be a bad director, doing Cookie☆ for the fame. Depending on who you ask either him or [[Maki (cookie)|]], the failed director, were the beginnings of the pessimism of the Cookie community.

title: agucala_(cookie)
body:
* !asset #21105161

Voice of [[Hakurei Reimu]] in [[cookie_(touhou)|Pepe☆]], [[Yakumo Yukari]] and [[Kirisame Marisa]] and Luna Child (as [[Riran Youkyu]]), 2019 [[Kochiya Sanae]] in Kuso☆☆☆☆☆☆. Her appearance as a [[dark-skinned female|dark-skinned]] Reimu with [[white gloves|white]] [[ribbon-trimmed gloves|ribbon-trimmed]] [[elbow gloves]], and [[no pants ]] is her most famous appearance, despite Pepe☆ generally being unremarkable. While playing a major role in Self-Contradiction☆, her depictions as Yukari and Marisa are less common. She has a very noticeable nasal lisp. 

The appearance of her dark-skinned Reimu and awkward speech made people joke that she was Filipino. Seems to be fairly unstable in their accounts, creating and deleting multiple YouTube and twitter accounts.

title: mugi_(cookie)
body:
* !asset #21103966

Voice of [[Hakurei Reimu]] in [[cookie_(touhou)|SpeCa☆]]. The only Reimu to have [[purple hair]] and a [[blue ascot]] and white [[hair tubes]] largely because of restrictions that were suddenly placed on the MMD model, so people started drawing fan art closer to PC98 Reimu. Like [[Kinu (cookie)|]] they originally pretended to be a woman but later admitted that he was a man. Was slightly jealous of how easily Kinu was able to have a feminine voice. 

While Kinu's admission of being a man was surprising and definitive, Mugi kept his gender relatively ambiguous for almost all of 2017, switching between male and female pronouns. This led to a lot of confusion over his gender since he had not released a video of his natural speaking voice yet, becoming the only voice actor to be called -aneki-aniki (姉貴兄貴). title: huban
body:
In ancient China, the sign held by officials when attending court was called "Hu Ban," also known as "Shou Ban," "Yu Ban," or "Chao Ban." It was a tool used by ancient Chinese subjects when facing the emperor.

In ancient times, when Chinese civil and military officials met the emperor, they held the Hu Ban in both hands to record the emperor's orders or intentions. They could also write down what they wanted to report to the emperor on the Hu Ban to prevent forgetting.

Officials of the fifth rank or higher held ivory Hu Ban, while officials of the sixth rank or lower held Hu Ban made of bamboo or wood. In the Ming Dynasty, it was stipulated that officials of the fifth rank or higher should hold ivory Hu Ban, while officials of the fifth rank or lower did not hold Hu Ban. Since the Qing Dynasty in China, the use of Hu Ban has been discontinued and abandoned.

title: defense_of_the_ancients
body:
[b]Defense of the Ancients[/b] (commonly known as [b]DotA[/b]) is a custom scenario for the real-time strategy game [[Warcraft III]] that became extremely popular. Valve would later buy the rights to DotA and create a sequel called [[Dota 2]] and a [[Dota (series)|series]].

The objective of the scenario is for each team to destroy the opponents' Ancients, heavily guarded structures at opposing corners of the map. Players are a part of a team of five, using powerful units known as Heroes and assisted by AI-controlled fighters called Creeps. 

h4. See also

* [[League of Legends]]
* [[Heroes of the Storm]]
* [[Heroes of Newerth]]

title: dota_2
body:
[i]DotA 2[/i] is an strategy video game developed by Valve Corporation. It is the sequel to the popular [i][[Warcraft III]] [/i] mod [i][[Defense of the Ancients]][/i], and the first entry in the Valve-run [[DotA (series)|]] franchise.

The game consists of session-based online multiplayer activity, with the primary objective of each match being for the teams to destroy their opposing team's fortified stronghold. Each player controls a player character called a "hero", who is given the responsibility of participating in team combat, which generally takes place along a series of lanes that connect their opposing bases, lined with defensive towers.

title: airbus_a350
body:
A long-range twin-engine wide-body airliner made by [b][[Airbus]][/b] in Toulouse, [[France]], which entered service in 2013 with Qatar Airways as its launch customer. It is the primary competitor with [[boeing|Boeing's]] [[boeing 787|787 Dreamliner]], featuring similar characteristics such as a lightweight composite fuselage, fuel-efficient high-bypass [[jet engine|turbofan engines]], a digital [[cockpit]], and improved cabin pressurization. Newer models also include electronically-dimming windows in lieu on pull-down window shades.

The A350-900ULR (Ultra-Long Range) variant has the longest range of any commercial airliner in service in the world at 9700 nm (17,900 km), which has resulted in it being used on the world's (current) longest commercial flight from [[New York City]] to [[Singapore]], taking 18 hours and 30 minutes. [[Qantas]] has selected a modified variant of the A350-1000 to be used on its upcoming [i]Project Sunrise[/i] route from [[Sydney]] to New York and [[London]], both flights upwards of 19 hours. [[Japan Airlines]] is also currently taking deliveries of the A350-1000 as its new long-haul flagship, replacing  the [[boeing 777|Boeing 777-300ER]]. 

Although the aircraft has a near-perfect safety record, it has had one hull loss--in "January 2024":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2024_Haneda_Airport_runway_collision]--when a JAL A350-900 collided with a [[Japan Coast Guard]] De Havilland Dash 8 on the runway of [[Haneda Airport]] in [[tokyo (city)|Tokyo]], resulting in the complete destruction of both aircraft. However investigations concluded that the incident was caused by a miscommunication with air traffic control rather than mechanical failure.
h4. See also

* [[List of airplanes]]
* [[boeing 787|Boeing 787 Dreamliner]], the A350's main competitor

h4. External links

body:
American [[instrument]] maker founded in 1883 in Brooklyn, [[New York City]] by German immigrant Friedrich Gretsch. While starting with [[banjo]]s [[tambourine]]s and [[drum]]s, the Gretch that is known today is most famously known for their hollow-body [[electric guitar]]s followed by its line of [i]Jet[/i] solid-body [[bass guitar]]s and electric guitars.
The name Gretsch starded gaining rapid success and popularity in the [[guitar]] market with the introduction of their now instantly recognisable large-scale hollow-body guitars in the mid and late 1950s with the growing success of the Country, Rockabily and Rock n' Roll in general as opposed to its relative competitors [[fender_musical_instruments_corporation|Fender]], [[gibson_brands_inc|Gibson]] and [[Rickenbacker]] being popular in more alternative (and often heavier) forms of music.

title: manhattan
body:
One of the five boroughs of [[new york city|New York City]] and is often considered the most well-known and iconic of the five. It is an island bordered by the "Hudson River":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hudson_River to the west, the "East River":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/East_River to the east, and separated from the mainland by various bridges and tunnels. 

Home to several prominent neighborhoods and landmarks, Manhattan is a significant hub for finance, commerce, culture, and tourism. Some of its famous neighborhoods include "Midtown Manhattan":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Midtown_Manhattan, which houses iconic places like [[Times Square]], "Broadway theaters":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Broadway_(Manhattan), and numerous skyscrapers; the "Upper East Side":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Upper_East_Side and "Upper West Side":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Upper_West_Side known for their residential areas and cultural institutions like the "Metropolitan Museum of Art":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metropolitan_Museum_of_Art and the "American Museum of Natural History":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American_Museum_of_Natural_History, respectively; and downtown districts like the "Financial District":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Financial_District,_Manhattan, which includes [[Wall Street]] and [[One World Trade Center]].

"Central Park":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Central_Park, one of the most famous urban parks in the world, spans a significant portion of Manhattan's midsection. Manhattan's neighborhoods showcase a blend of historic architecture, modern skyscrapers, cultural diversity, and a vibrant social scene, making it a bustling and diverse area within New York City.

h4. External links
* "Wikipedia: Manhattan":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Manhattan]

title: world_trade_center
body:
A large complex of seven [[building]]s in the Financial District of Lower Manhattan in [[New York City]] [[City]] that originally stood from 1973 to 2001. More often referred to as the [b]Twin Towers[/b], in reference to its two tallest buildings, a pair of landmark buildings that stood there. The center was targeted as part of a terrorist attack on [[9/11|September 11, 2001]], leading to the destruction of the Twin Towers.

A new complex was built on the site of the old one, including such sites as the National September 11 Memorial and buildings as the [[One World Trade Center]].

title: miguel_o'hara
body:
A fictional character in the [[Marvel]] universe. He first appeared in 1992 as the superhero [[Spider-Man (2099)|Spider-Man 2099]]. 

Miguel O'Hara is a geneticist working for the mega-corporation Alchemax in a future version of [[new york city|New York City]] called Nueva York. After an accident, Miguel undergoes a genetic transformation to acquire spider-like abilities similar to the original [[Spider-Man]], including enhanced strength, agility, and the ability to stick to walls. As Spider-Man 2099, Miguel fights crime and corruption in the dystopian future, often facing challenges unique to his time period.

title: christ_the_redeemer
body:
[b]Christ the Redeemer[/b] (Portuguese: [i]Cristo Redentor[/i]) is a 30-meter-high concrete [[Art Deco]] [[statue]] of [[Jesus|Christ]] that stands atop the [[Brazil|Brazilian]] mountain Corcovado, overlooking the city of [[Rio de Janeiro]].

Christ the Redeemer's distinctive look and dramatic setting have made it an icon of the city since its completion in 1931. An artist wanting to establish that an image involves Rio has only to include it in the background somewhere, in much the same way that, for instance, the [[Eiffel Tower]] instantly evokes [[Paris]], or the [[Statue of Liberty]] does [[New York City]].

h4. External links

title: man_of_la_mancha
body:
[quote][i]"To dream the impossible dream
To fight the unbeatable foe
To bear with unbearable sorrow
To run where the brave dare not go..."[/i] - A fragment from [b]The Impossible Dream[/b] by "Andy Williams":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andy_Williams, main theme of the movie.[/quote]

A 1972 theatrical musical film adaptation of a 1965 musical play based on the novel [[Don Quixote (novel)|]]. It stars "Peter O'Toole":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peter_O%27Toole as [[Alonso Quixano]], "Sophia Loren":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sophia_Loren as [[Dulcinea del Toboso]] and "James Coco":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/James_Coco as [[Sancho Panza]].

h4. See also
* "Official Trailer":https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=q-FRZcQ4qVE

* [[Don Quixote (Project MOON)]]

title: rocinante
body:
[b]Rocinante[/b] ([[spanish_text|Spanish]] pronunciation: [roθiˈnante]) is [[alonso quixano|Don Quijote]]'s horse in the two-part 1605/1615 novel [[Don Quixote (novel)|]] by Miguel de Cervantes. 

In many ways, Rocinante is not only his [[horse]], but also his double; like Don Quijote, he is awkward, skinny, past his prime, and engaged in a task beyond his capacities.

title: spanish_text
body:
The image contains text written in the Spanish language.

Spanish is the language of the European country of [[Spain]] (where it originated) as well as several Latin American countries like [[Mexico]], [[Argentina]], [[Colombia]], [[Venezuela]], [[Cuba]], [[Chile]], [[Peru]], etc. Also used in the East Asian country of The [[Philippines]].

h4. See also

title: nakahara_masaru
body:
Main character of [[Bacchikoi!]]. He is one of the two love interests the player ([[Kanada Toshu]]) can pursue.

He is Yakyusha Academy baseball club's captain. Alongide baseball, Masaru can also play the piano, as he was taught by his mother, who was deceased. His mother died due to terminal illness, for which his family tried to collect and save money to cure, which resulted in his family becoming completely bankrupt and entering many debts. He also failed many exams at his school, which almost led him to lose his scholarship and leave the baseball club.

title: nene_nene
body:
Nene Nene (literally, "Root-sound Nene") is an [[UTAU]]LOID female as a singing [[plant girl]]. She was made by Musumesaibou-P, and drawn by [[Tokita (jyabarachan)|]].

Her official hairstyle is "fake [[bob cut]]" in a broad sense. She wears [[serafuku]] and [[headphones]]. And she has a flower[[pot]] as optional accessories. She is characterized with a big [[flower]] of her right wrist, and her lower body which has [[plant roots]] instead of her feet. She can move by crawling with her roots. Her catchphrase is "the singing voice crawling on the ground".

Her flower has the function of a [[speaker]], and her mouth has the function of an audio-jack. When she sings a song, she connects a cord to her flower and holds the audio-plug of the cord in her mouth. She likes little girls and dislikes insects.

title: xiphos_(sword)
body:
The [b]Xiphos[/b] (Ancient Greek: (το) ξίφος) is a leaf-shaped double-edged, single-handed short [[sword]] used by the ancient Greek [[hoplite]] warriors. 

It was always a secondary battlefield weapon for the Greek armies after the [[spear]] (their main weapon), used only when the spear was lost in battle.

title: oracle_(ancient_greece)
body:
In the ancient Greek culture an [b]Oracle[/b] was a holy person who became [[drugged]] by inhaling the fumes from sacred caves or rock formations, or by smoking and consuming ritual herbs, mushrooms or other natural [[drugs]].

This state supposedly enabled these people to communicate with the Gods and to see events in the far distant future.

title: green_tea_(cookie)
body:
* !asset #21093235

Voice of [[Yatadera Narumi]] in [[Cookie (touhou)|Zapper☆]] and specifically Narumi in nearly every voice drama she has acted in, and director of Gyudon☆. Started posting MADs of [[JOKER (cookie)|]] and [[Akanuma]] too eventually working with JOKER on Gyudon☆. Also seemed to be partially multilingual, translating a few Chinese voice dramas and reaching out to [[Maru (cookie)|]] and [[Web (cookie)|]]. Started slowing down posting in August 2020 and completely disappeared in 2023, with some guessing that she might have died of an unknown chronic disease she had.

Her involvement in nearly every part of both the Cookie and [[Manatsu no yo no Inmu|Inmu]] communities made her stand out more than most of the other voice actresses. Her preference for heterosexual pairings was considered extremely unusual and she became one of the most divisive creators on the entirety of NicoNico. She was sent a dick pic in twitter DMs and then proceeded to grade it so she is sometimes drawn as obsessed with dicks or generally lewd.

Voice of [[Alice Margatroid]] in [[Cookie (touhou)|Zapper☆]] and a decently large amount of other voice dramas. She was initially well respected for being fairly good acting, singing, and talking. However, her avatar became more known when she started issuing takedowns on MADs that she didn't like. When the 2018 Hokkaido Eastern Iburi earthquake happened, people created MADs to see if she would take them down to see if she was still alive. Her name means [[Scorpion]] Princess so fans like to draw her as an angry scorpion, stinging everyone.

title: bacchikoi!

[[Yaoi]] [[visual novel]] from [[BlackMonkey Pro]], released on September 6th, 2014.

The main story follows a Yakyusha Academy transfer student [[Kanada Toshu]], who joins it's baseball club and plays it alongside [[Nakahara Masaru]], the club's captain, and [[Yanai Ichiru]], both of which are potential love interests in the main game.

Bacchikoi!'s expansion pack - "Bacchikoi Expansion Pack", released in July 11th, 2015, features different stories in the same timeline as the original game, focusing more on Yakyusha's baseball club captain [[Tadano Genji]], [[Nakahara Masaru|Masaru]] and [[Yanai Ichiru|Ichiru]] rather than [[Kanada Toshu|Toshu]]. The expansion pack does not offer players any choice and can only scroll through the single variant story featured in the expansion pack.

An American voice actress who lives in the state of Georgia, she is mostly drawn as Alice or "Miji". Highly regarded for her upbeat and energetic voice acting. Now active as the [[virtual youtuber]] [[Webemez]].

Being the main character of Easter☆ combined with the novelty of the first fully English Cookie voice drama made her the popular star in any following MADs and remixes. Her lines "Oh, no!", "Don't worry!", "Yayyyyyy", "What a wonderful morning", and "Oh wow" are simple enough for most Japanese users to understand so are used the most often. Her depiction of Miji completed the Cerberus with [[INU (cookie)|]] and [[Kuso Inu (cookie)|]]. A sub-meme of her as a [[ninja]] got popular for some reason.

title: v2_assault-buster_gundam
body:
A fictional [[mecha]] from the [[Gundam]] series. It first appeared in [[Victory Gundam]] from 1993-1994.

[b]LM314V23/24 Assault-Buster Gundam[/b]

The almost invincible configuration of the [[V2 Gundam]] [[mobile suit]]. Equipped with the Assault Package, consisting of add-on reactive armor, I-Field generators on the shoulders, a pair of Variable Speed Beam Rifles on the hips, and a mega beam rifle, and the Buster Package, fitting a mega beam cannon, beam spray pod, and micro-missile launchers, the V2's tremendous base combat capabilities are expanded both offensively and defensively, enabling the unit to fight with the combat effectiveness of an entire squad. The full configuration was only briefly deployed by [[Uso Ewin]] before an accurate shot by [[Katejina Loos]] destroyed the Buster add-on parts.

title: hisaka_(cookie)
body:
* !asset #21091648

Voice of [[Remilia Scarlet]] in [[cookie_(touhou)|Clownpiece☆]]. Identifiable by her [[purple eyes]] and [[purple hair]] and never smiling. Usually animated extremely oddly, with a focus on [[body horror]]. Became well known for documenting her depressing life on twitter but has mostly been positive recently.

She's elaborated on a few different incidents in her life that are depicted in art:
* She eats [[taiyaki]] from the center first
* She drew a picture of [[Izayoi Sakuya]] that looked like it had tentacles for arms. This Sakuya is called Hisakuya.
* [[Dorasiro (cookie)|]]: A male fan of hers, a few years older than her. Talked with her during her depressive episodes. 
* Her brother poured boiling water on her
* A cat attacked her on the way home from shopping and stole her fish
* She's had multiple minor fractures
* A random boy beat her with a baseball bat
* She dropped the baton during a relay race and was bullied for days
* Her friend strangles her regularly

title: tearju_lunatique
body:
A character featured in both [[black_cat_(series)|Black Cat]] and [[To LOVE-Ru Darkness]], sharing the same name and looks in both. Tearju wears [[glasses]], has [[very long hair|very long]] [[blonde hair]] and [[green eyes]].

In Black Cat, she was the lead researcher on the nanotechnology project that created [[eve_(black_cat)|Eve]], having used her own DNA as a base.

In To Love Ru, she is a new teacher at [[Yuuki Rito]]'s school and an old friend of [[Mikado Ryouko]].  [spoiler]Is also a former biologist and delivered the genes for the creation of [[Konjiki no Yami]]. In other words, she is Yami's "mother".[/spoiler]

Also has done a few voices for the [[Touhou M-1 Grand Prix]]. Fairly standard appearance as Hata-tan, identifiable by her giant hat with a [[green bow]] as Marisa. Voice of [[Inubashiri Momiji]] and [[Cirno]] in [[cookie_(touhou)|Kuso Inu☆]]. Identifiable by her [[shaded face]], [[floppy ears]], and [[evil smile]]. Like [[Jigen (cookie)|]], her screen name is Shukuren but everyone calls her Kuso Inu. One of the most convincing voice actresses, she became the most popular of the voice drama/doujin. 

Her line "Isn't free food received without having to work delicious? Haha, I wonder if Momiji would be able to eat it...” is her most famous. Usually appears as a bully in fan art. title: green_little_pig_(sinoalice)
body:
One of the Three Little Pig [[sisters]]. The three have very similar designs but there exists several distinguishable traits. She is the one with a [[plump]] body, bangs parted to the right and [[double bun]]. She is associated with the color green.

The Three Little Pigs act as a single character in gameplay, sharing almost all of their character sprites. The one in the center receives a new art with each skin like other characters, while the two on the back follows a pose template and only have their clothes changed. The [[Red Little Pig (sinoalice)|]] is almost always the "central character":/posts/7175966, but the Green Little Pigs has received a "central sprite":/posts/3736358 as well as a "solo sprite":/posts/3941679.

Director of the second trilogy of [[cookie (touhou)|Cookie☆]] voice dramas (Halloween☆, Nabe☆, and Myorenji☆), semi-professional [[League of Legends]] player. Following the conclusion of [[Taisa (cookie)|]]'s Cookie Season 2, there was excitement for who next would be taking their chances directing a series of voice dramas. Maki was hyped to be the next big star, however all three of his voice dramas flopped for being too boring in both the voice drama itself and any controversy. Maki's legacy is largely as a failed director, and the fear of being the next Maki became a running theme in following voice dramas.

title: game_club_project
body:
A group of [[Virtual YouTuber]]s operated by Unlimited (now known as Brave Group) that started activity on 6 March 2018. 

In April 2019, there was a controversy regarding an internal problem between the voices portraying the club members and the management, leading to them being fired. They later resumed their activities on 19 April after a discussion among the voices and managements, but towards the end of 2019, they were all replaced with a new set of voices causing a negative reception that disbanded the group in February 2021.

Eventually Kaede, Ryou, Miria, and Cocoa's original voices moved [[Yuzuriha Honami|on]] [[Yuugasaki Umi|to]] [[Hanagumo Kuyuri|other]] "projects":[https://www.youtube.com/@AliAofficial], Haruto similarly so. Cocoa's new voice actor was transferred off the project to concentrate on her virtual artist career, while Miria's new voice actor would be transferred to a new agency, Highway Star, along with fellow Unlimited coworker [[Claire Cruller]]. 

h4. Characters

title: crew_neck
body:
A type of [[shirt]], [[sweater]], [[dress]], or other top with a round, close-fitting neckline. The crew neck gets its name from its association with rowing teams and other athletic crews who originally wore this style of shirt.

h4. Characteristics:

* [b]Shape:[/b] The defining feature of a crew neck is its round, circular neckline. It does not have a collar and is typically higher than other necklines, such as a [[V-neck]] or [[scoop neck]].
* [b]Fit:[/b] The neckline sits snugly around the base of the neck without any plunging or revealing cuts.

h4. Related Tags:
* [[V-neck]]: For garments with a V-shaped neckline.
* [[scoop neck]]: For garments with a wide, rounded neckline that is lower than a crew neck.
* [[turtleneck]]: For garments with a high, close-fitting collar that covers the neck.

title: izumi-no-kami_kanesada
body:
A [i][[Touken Ranbu]][/i] character, the personification of the historical [[katana|uchigatana]] [i]Izumi-no-Kami Kanesada[/i]. 
Character designed by [[Shiramine (srmn09)|]], voiced by [[Kimura Ryouhei]]. 

He was formerly classified by the game as a tachi until July 2015. Both he and [[Horikawa Kunihiro]] are personifications of swords that belonged to [[Hijikata Toshizou]] of the [[Shinsengumi]]. He was asked to be made after the Shinsengumi started to become well known, and Hijikata thus sought after a swordsmith from the Kanesada school, requesting that his new sword be similar to his [[wakizashi]] (Horikawa). This is likely the reason why Izumi-no-kami and Horikawa have the same hair and eye color. He is still around today, located in the Hijikata Toshizou Museum in his hometown of Hino, [[Tokyo (city)|]].

h4. Appearance
[tn]See post #1934098 for base form.[/tn]

He has [[long hair|long]] [[black hair]] with part of it done in a [[side braid]], and [[blue eyes]]. He typically wears [[earrings]], [[Japanese clothes]], black [[fingerless gloves]], and a [[cape]] with the Shinsengumi's distinctive blue and white pattern. For his [[Izumi-no-kami Kanesada (Kiwame)|Kiwame]] form, he puts his hair up in a [[ponytail]] and wears a white [[headband]], a Shinsengumi [[haori]] and black [[knee boots]]. 

Despite looking like an adult, he is technically the youngest character in the game, being the most recently forged sword as he was made in 1867. Because of this, he often comes across as reckless and a bit overconfident, which is why Horikawa often has to assist him or reign him in. Much of his personality is also inspired by the real-life Hijikata.

h4. Alternate outfits/forms
* !post #1934099: Alternate
* !post #2891421: [[Izumi-no-kami Kanesada (Kiwame)|Kiwame form]]

title: asura_(mythology)
body:
A mythological race of demonic beings which feature prominently in [[Hindu mythology]] and [[Buddhism]]. They are primarily malevolent, and are in a constant struggle against the gods for power. However some benevolent asuras also exist, which are typically depicted as protectors of justice and destroyers of evil.

They are usually depicted with [[extra faces|multiple faces]] (typically four placed around a single head) and [[extra arms]] (typically four or eight). Each face may express a different emotion.

title: ichigo_(cookie)
body:
* !asset #21073780
* !asset #21073781: ASKICG

Voice of [[Alice Margatroid]] in [[Atouda Ako (character)|]]'s [[cookie_(touhou)|Kuso☆☆☆]]. Instantly became popular for her incredibly soft-spoken and weak voice. Was never very active in the Cookie community and left during the Cookie Freeze Festival of 2018 where several directors and actresses had false DMCA's end their twitter and NND accounts. However in 2020 a fan discovered her new twitter account and another fan named Ryo-IchigoKnight, a middle school girl, doxxed her leading Ichigo to delete her account. Three weeks later Ryo committed suicide by train on the Tobo-Tojo line.

Ichigo's depiction is almost entirely based on fan art instead of her personal life or actions in the voice drama. She has an unusually high amount of memes due to how popular Kuso☆☆☆ became.
* Her most famous scene was her buying ingredients at a store owned by [[Nyon (cookie)|]] while [[Akira (cookie)|]] rambled about the history of Valentine's day. Her [[desk slam|slamming the counter]] and telling Nyon "Why don't you quit this job!?" when Nyon didn't have any ingredients became the most famous. 
* NYNICG became her most popular ship because of this. MADs featuring their adventures are now some of Cookie's most popular videos.
* Her line "Ikuyo!" also became famous and copied, usually paired with the thrusters with [[arrow (symbol)|]]s on them from [[Algodoo]] based on an [[Manatsu no yo no Inmu|Inmu]] series of MADs. 
* Ichigo was a fan of [[Miffy]], and combined with Alice being a puppeteer and the Aldogoo thrusters, she began to be drawn as [[telekinesis|telekinetic]]. She is usually see controlling her [[stuffed rabbit]], [[Fluffy fluffy Rabbit-chan]].
* She joined the ALC Faction with the other famous Alices, but in particular started getting paired with [[Jigen (cookie)|]]. 
* Some [[graffiti]] of her appeared on an abandoned building in Kanagawa: https://archive.is/gNL5z
* Her alternate appearance as ASKICG came from an interview video she did. Instead of Alice, she appears as a girl with [[long hair|long]] [[brown hair]], a [[strawberry hair ornament|strawberry]] [[red hairband|hairband]], a [[pink capelet]] with a [[purple necktie]], and a [[green dress]].
* MADs of her dancing to [[Mettaton]]'s theme went viral.

title: hotaruda_(cookie)
body:
* !asset #21073035

A derivative character that combined [[Shinonome (cookie)|]] and [[Sakenomi (cookie)|]]. "Hotaru" means firefly, as a reference to how Eirin stuck a flashlight up Reimu's ass in the original voice drama. Got more popular after appearing in [[OFFSide: DIYUSI]] and is now drawn more with those characters than Shinonome herself.

title: shinonome_(cookie)
body:
* !asset #21073001

Voice of [[Hakurei Reimu]] in [[Atouda Ako (character)|]]'s [[cookie_(touhou)|Kuso☆☆]] with her name based on [[professor_shinonome|Shinonome Hakase]]. Identifiable by her [[black hair]] and [[black eyes]] with [[white pupils]] and a [[lab coat]]. Says she largely regrets doing Cookie voice acting since it makes all Touhou secondary works look bad. 

Her role in the voice drama was Reimu who needed to get her ass checked, but fan works like to depict her as the doctor as the other members of the voice drama had more popular roles elsewhere. Running jokes about her usually involve her ass [[glowing]], a [[peach]] since it is ass-shaped, or as a mad [[scientist]]. Spawned the Sakenomi-like [[Hotaruda (cookie)|]].

title: yayoi_usagi
body:
* !asset #21072940

Voice of [[Alice Margatroid]] in [[Atouda Ako (character)|]]'s [[cookie_(touhou)|Kuso☆]]. Also disappeared soon after the voice drama aired, but came back a few years later. After a random Russian used her old twitter name and revealing she was from Shiga prefecture where the original [[ninja]]s were from, fans began to draw her as a ninja using the sarashi she wore in the voice drama as a mask.

title: mai_(cookie)
body:
* !asset #21072933


Voice of [[Patchouli Knowledge]] in [[Atouda Ako (character)|]]'s [[cookie_(touhou)|Kuso☆]]. There was a rumor that she was a foreigner so her name is written in all lowercase like the cast of Easter☆. Disappeared almost immediately after the voice drama came out, taking [[Yuwo (cookie)|]]'s title of "Cookie's fastest woman".

title: mikami_makoto
body:
* !asset #21072849
* !asset #21072858
* !asset #21072876

Voice of [[Kirisame Marisa]] in [[Atouda Ako (character)|]]'s [[cookie_(touhou)|Kuso☆]], she has also been involved in every level of several dozen other voice dramas by planning, directing, drawing, singing, remixing, writing, and [[Vocaloid]] producing. While initially unpopular due to the many other Marisas and having a small part in Kuso☆, her popular and acting skill grew with every production she did. Now works as a freelance music producer for other dramas.

Her appearance in Kuso☆ was mostly overshadowed by [[Noel (cookie)|]] but her following voice dramas slowly built her popularity, especially since her chain-smoker voice was unique. She is a fan of [[military]] dramas, and is now most often depicted as Marisa in a [[military uniform]]. For a while she used a picture of [[Tatara Kogasa]] with an [[eyepatch]] as her avatar on twitter. Her work as an R18 voice and skill with video editing usually means people hold her in higher regard than most other actresses.

title: koutari_yuu
body:
A [[Black_Rock_Shooter|Black★Rock Shooter]] character, sharing physical characteristics with her other form [[Strength_(black_rock_shooter)|STR]]. Voiced by [[Asumi Kana]].

h4. Appearance
She is consistently portrayed with [[short hair|short]] [[brown hair]] and [[brown eyes]], plus being the shortest of the franchise's main characters. 

* !post #719432: 2010 version
* !post #1034770: 2012 version

In the 2010 OVA, she is portrayed with a white [[serafuku]] and [[blue sailor collar]], blue [[neckerchief]], and [[blue skirt]], the same outfit as her classmates.

title: boku_no_kanojo_sensei
body:
[b]Boku no Kanojo Sensei[/b] (My Teacher-Girlfriend, 僕のカノジョ先生) is a romcom light novel series, written by Yuu Kagami (鏡遊), and illustrated by [[oryo (oryo04)|oryo]] (おりょう). It is now a completed series with nine volumes. A manga adaptation illustrated by [[sdwing]] began publication in 2019 and is currently ongoing.

The story revolves around the protagonist [[Saiki Makoto]], who has a distrust for teachers because of a past traumatic experience. One day he was confessed to by his teacher, [[Fujiki Maka]]. Ever since then she has been using every method she knows in order to pursue him in a form of “guidance counseling”.

body:
The titular [[super robot]] [[mecha]] from the [[Megas XLR]] American animated TV show from 2004.

[b]MEGAS XLR[/b] stands for [b]M[/b]echanized [b]E[/b]arth [b]G[/b]uard [b]A[/b]ttack [b]S[/b]ystem e[b]X[/b]tra [b]L[/b]arge [b]R[/b]obot.

This robot is very powerful and has many weapons. It uses a [[muscle car]] as main cockpit, specifically an unlicensed approximation of a [[Plymouth Barracuda]], as they were unable to license the real car. 

The [[steering wheel]] of the car is actually used to control Megas, just like the [[Boss Borot]] robot from the old [[Mazinger Z]] Japanese anime series (probably as a tribute).

title: hong_kong_97
body:
A legendarily bad unlicensed video game for the [[Super Nintendo]], released in 1995. You play as Chin, [[Bruce Lee]]'s "relative", who is actually played by [[Jackie Chan]], and are tasked with killing 1.2 billion Mainland Chinese who invade during the 1997 handover of Hong Kong from the British Empire to communist China. After 5 minutes of a terrible [[danmaku]] game, [[Deng Xiaoping]] appears as a disembodied head to fight you. Also notable is the 3 second loop of "I love Beijing Tianamen":[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mJmjljQP3oY] [i]with lyrics[/i] that replays endlessly even through loading screens.

The game went viral in the 2000s in gaming circles, and reached mass attention after being reviewed on [[Angry Video Game Nerd]] in 2015. More on the game's development and background, especially in relation to its creator, would be uncovered on Ultra Healthy Video Game Nerd.

title: portrait_of_king_charles_iii_(jonathan_yeo)
body:
The first official portrait of [[Charles III|King Charles III]] since his coronation in May 2023. The portrait, done by artist Jonathan Yeo, features Charles' face while his body blends into a bright [[red background]]. The portrait drew strong reactions and jokes on social media, with some claiming it looked demonic, as though Charles was in the fires of hell. After emerging online in mid-May 2024, the artwork inspired numerous memes using it as an [[fine art parody|exploitable]] format.

h4.External links
* "Jonathan Yeo - HM King Charles III":https://www.jonathanyeo.com/king-charles-iii
* "Know Your Meme: King Charles' Portrait":https://knowyourmeme.com/memes/king-charles-portrait

title: nerf_dart
body:
Nerf darts are the catch-all term for any dart projectiles in the [[Hasbro]]-owned [[toy gun]] franchise Nerf. As many different Nerf guns utilise different types of ammunition, the term 'Nerf dart' specifically refers to small, cylindrical tubes topped with rubber ends that are designed to be a kid-friendly imitation of [[bullet|bullets]] for use in mock firefights.

The most universally recognised type of Nerf dart is the "Elite Dart":[https://nerf.fandom.com/wiki/Elite_Dart], a category of Nerf dart that was first released in 2012 coinciding with the launch of the N-Strike Elite series of Nerf toy guns. The standard Elite Dart is recognised by its [[blue]] cylindrical body and [[orange]] rubber tip, which has a hole inside it, likely to prevent choking if it were to be consumed. 

These Elite Darts were designed to be direct improvements to the previous 'Streamline Dart', with upgades to their range, aerodynamic stability, and general accuracy. However, they share largely the same flaws as their Streamline predecessor, primarily the hole in the front causing the air in front of the bullet, as it naturally encounters air resistance, to be dragged through the hollow body of the bullet, deforming and thus unbalancing the dart. 

Hasbro continues to manufacture these darts in spite of this design flaw in order to assure the safety of children who may consume the bullet accidentally, as despite their resemblance to conventional bullets fired by conventional firearms, Nerf ammunition, like the rest of the brand, is designed for non-lethal play instead of live fire combat. As such, their efficiency in both killing and as a general projectile are not prioritised.

The universality of the Elite Dart's design has resulted in many color variants being produced for Nerf toy weapons outside the initial N-Strike Series, such as the "GlowStrike Dart":[https://nerf.fandom.com/wiki/GlowStrike_Dart] (which would glow in the dark), the "Message Dart":[https://nerf.fandom.com/wiki/Message_Dart] (which was packaged with equipment that allowed for the writing of messages on the dart's body), and the "Star Wars Dart":[https://nerf.fandom.com/wiki/Star_Wars_Dart] (a collaboration dart produced for the [[Star Wars]] crossover line which came in [[red]] and [[blue]] colors signifying allegience to the First Order and the Resistance respectively).

title: mii_gunner_(smash_ultimate)
body: The [[Mii Gunner]] from [i]Super Smash Bros. Ultimate[/i]. She has grayish brown hair and eyes. She swaps out the orange for yellow, and instead wears a cool cropped jacket with coordinating footwear to boot. She was initially completely forgettable amidst the largest Smash Bros. cast of all time, but after the announcement of a certain [[Sans (undertale)|DLC costume]], she has since been subjected to a relentless amount of memes. Mostly being about how she would be completely forgettable if it wasn't for her donning [[Sans (Undertale)|someone else's]] likeness.

title: oonishi_ryuusei
body:
[[Oonishi Ryuusei]] is a Japanese idol, actor, and television personality. He is a member of the male idol group NANIWA DANSHI.
Born on August 7, 1997, in Hyogo Prefecture, Japan, Ohnishi joined Johnny & Associates talent agency in July 2012.
He has a strong background in dance and serves as the group’s sub-leader.

title: shinn_asuka
body:
The protagonist of [[Gundam SEED Destiny]] - a young man who lost his family, victims of stray fire during one of [[Kira Yamato]]'s interventions, and chose to join ZAFT and enact his personal vengeance against the pilot of the [[Freedom Gundam]]. He takes to the controls of the [[Impulse Gundam]] - fittingly for his impulsive and enraged nature - in order to destroy Kira, but later abandons the suit and continues to fight his nemesis as the pilot of the [[Destiny Gundam]]. Both Shinn and Kira reconciled with each other at the end of the series. He eventually becomes the boyfriend of [[Lunamaria Hawke]].

In [[Gundam SEED Freedom]], he now serves as Kira's right-hand man, and becomes the designated pilot of the [[Immortal Justice Gundam]]. After the suit's destruction, he is once again, the pilot of the now upgraded [[Destiny Gundam Spec II]].

title: io_fleming
body:
One of the main characters in [[Gundam Thunderbolt]], Io Fleming is a brash thrill-seeking ace pilot with a love of free jazz.

He pilots the [[Full Armor Gundam]] and the [[Atlas Gundam]].

Voiced by [[Nakamura Yuuichi]] (JP) and Max Mittleman (EN).

title: siyudi_(cookie)
body:
* !asset #21050088

A derivative character of [[DIYUSI (cookie)|]], spawned from the popularity of DIYUSI's [[Cookie (touhou)|Cookie☆]] MADs. She has [[black hair]] in a [[high ponytail]] with a [[red bow|red]] [[hair bow]], [[red eyes]], [[white skin]] and wears a [[collared shirt|collared]] [[white shirt]] with [[long sleeves]], a [[red ascot]], a [[black skirt|black]] [[suspender skirt]], and [[holding umbrella|holds]] a [[red umbrella|red]] [[closed umbrella]].

Whether or not she was accepted as a Cookie☆ character was controversial, as she was a completely original character with no attached voice drama. Over time, she has been slowly accepted as a part of DIYUSI's group as DIYUSI herself is barely a Touhou character anymore.

Sometimes has a similar treatment to [[yukkuri abuse]] but not very popular. Now paired with [[Hotaruda (cookie)|]], a similar minigirl version of [[Shinonome (cookie)|]].

title: rie-chan
body:
[i]An 18 year old girl that is enrolled in a clothing design school.
She is a big fan of SUGI-kun and is in love with his sweet singing voice from Shibuya.
She's actually crazy for the British rock bands of the 80s, as well.[/i]

Rie♥chan is an 18 year old clothing designer who owns multiple brands. She is Japanese, but loves traveling the world to find different types of music. Plays [[guitar]] and collects [[records]]. In her most recent appearances she has been seen working in a [[cafe]].

Friend of [[Sanae-chan]] and [[belle_(pop'n_music)|Belle]]. 
Has a crush on [[Sugi-kun]]
